    "minides": "Renault's sub-4m value SUV, refreshed with new Renault logo, sporty bumpers, dual-tone alloys, ventilated front seats, 360-degree camera, 6 standard airbags, and wireless connectivity — all at India's most aggressive price point in the segment.",
    "description": "The Renault Kiger facelift launched in August 2025 with a redesigned front featuring Renault's latest logo, a sportier grille and bumpers, new dual-tone 16-inch alloy wheels, and smoked tail lamps. The interior now has a dual-tone black-and-light-grey finish, ventilated front seats, a 360-degree surround view camera, auto headlamps, rain-sensing wipers, and an 8-inch touchscreen with wireless Android Auto and Apple CarPlay. Two engines are offered: a 1.0-litre naturally aspirated petrol (72 PS, 96 Nm) available with a 5-speed manual or 5-speed AMT, and a 1.0-litre turbo petrol (100 PS, 160 Nm) paired with either a 5-speed manual or a CVT. Six airbags are now standard across all variants. The Kiger is positioned below the Tata Nexon, Maruti Brezza, Hyundai Venue, and Skoda Kylaq on price, making it the most affordable feature-rich sub-compact SUV option. No sunroof is offered on any variant."
  },
